         <abstract>
            <p>Although earnings per share is easy to understand and simple to calculate, the corporation that bases key financial decisions on this criterion risks severely misallocating its resources and shortchanging its common shareholders. Instead, the author suggests basing such decisions on a new criterion called Free Cash Flow.</p>
